<subSubSection pageId="117" pageNumber="118" type="distinguishing features">
<paragraph pageId="117" pageNumber="118">Distinguishing features.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="117" pageNumber="118">
This hybrid differs from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="L., Sp. Pl. 1: 156. 1753. (Linnaeus" authorityYear="1753" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Convolvulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Convolvulus siculus" order="Solanales" pageId="117" pageNumber="118" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="siculus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="117" pageNumber="118">Convolvulus siculus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in its oblong-spathulate leaves attenuate at the base and from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Jacq., Collectanea 4: 209. 1791. (Jacquin" authorityYear="1791" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Convolvulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Convolvulus humilis" order="Solanales" pageId="117" pageNumber="118" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="humilis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="117" pageNumber="118">Convolvulus humilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the upper leaves lanceolate, narrowed, not rounded at the apex.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="117" pageNumber="118" type="distribution">
<paragraph pageId="117" pageNumber="118">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="117" pageNumber="118">Found once in Libya (Cyrenaica).</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
